On 7/18/05 8:16 AM, "Ian" <ianj(-at-)whro.net> wrote:

> the only one I have removed was from and early 76 and if I remember the
> hinge was attached with a screws to the body. But they did change them so
> some are welded but I dont know if it was ealy one that were welded or the
> later ones.

Look under the seal and you've find two screws holding the hinges on. Scrape
away the paint because they are phillips head and use an impact driver to
loosen them.

